## 1. Where AI actually fits in SEO content

AI is most useful in **multiple stages** of the content workflow, not just “writing the article.” 

- Research  
  - Analyze top-ranking content and SERPs to see structure, topics, and gaps. 
  - Cluster keywords into pillars and supporting posts to build topical authority. 

- Outlining  
  - Generate outlines based on search intent and competitor analysis.  
  - Include H2/H3s, FAQs, and suggested internal links. 

- Drafting  
  - Create first drafts that cover 70–80% of the final content so writers never face a blank page. 
  - Add examples and section ideas that can be refined later.

- Optimization  
  - Score drafts for on-page SEO, readability, and semantic coverage. 
  - Suggest schema, meta descriptions, headings, and internal links.

- Refreshing & repurposing  
  - Flag decaying content and propose updates.  
  - Turn blogs into social posts, emails, FAQs, and scripts to maximize ROI. 
