## 3. Guardrails and “never do this” rules

The strongest experts repeat similar warnings. 

- Never publish AI content without edit  
  - A human editor must add real experience, checks, and brand voice before anything goes live. 

- Avoid generic AI blog spam  
  - Thin, unoriginal AI content may rank briefly but hurts trust and long-term authority.
- Always connect content to business goals  
  - Content should map to clear intent (awareness, consideration, BOFU) and real revenue metrics, not just traffic numbers. 

